---
import heatmapData from '../../data/B2/bloque_2_heatmap_mineral_metodo.json'
import B2HeatmapMineralMetodo from '../../components/charts/B2HeatmapMineralMetodo'
---

<section class="b2h-section w-[80%] mx-auto border-l border-r border-white/20">
  <div class="b2h-inner">
    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="b2h-header">
      <span class="b2h-badge">BLOCK 02 · GENERAL OVERVIEW</span>
      <h2 class="b2h-title">Mineral and Method: Complete Overview</h2>
      <p class="b2h-subtitle">
        Heat map crossing the 10 main minerals with the 4 extraction method states. The "Unknown"
        column reveals how much information is missing per mineral — conditioning the reliability of
        all subsequent analysis.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Heatmap chart -->
    <div class="b2h-chart-wrapper">
      <B2HeatmapMineralMetodo data={heatmapData} client:only="react" />
    </div>

    <!-- Contextual insight -->
    <div class="b2h-insight">
      <span class="b2h-insight__icon">🔍</span>
      <p class="b2h-insight__text">
        <strong>Iron</strong> (92%) and <strong>Bentonite</strong> (89%) have the highest levels of unknown
        data. In contrast, <strong>Antimony</strong> has the smallest gap (68%), allowing a more reliable
        analysis of its distribution by method. In Peru, the high number of mining concessions —many still
        in early stages such as exploration— partly explains the lack of detailed information on extraction
        methods. This gap does not imply inactivity, but rather reflects projects undergoing technical
        development, whose information will consolidate as they advance toward more defined stages of
        exploitation.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .b2h-section {
    padding: 80px 0 60px;
    background: var(--bg-primary);
  }

  .b2h-inner {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  /* Header */
  .b2h-header {
    margin-bottom: 40px;
  }

  .b2h-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    color: var(--accent-lime);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    padding: 4px 14px;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: rgba(193, 214, 91, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(193, 214, 91, 0.15);
  }

  .b2h-title {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    letter-spacing: -0.5px;
  }

  .b2h-subtitle {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Chart wrapper */
  .b2h-chart-wrapper {
    padding: 24px;
    border-radius: 16px;
    background: var(--glass-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--glass-border);
    backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  /* Insight */
  .b2h-insight {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 14px;
    padding: 20px 24px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    background: rgba(132, 98, 72, 0.06);
    border: 1px solid rgba(132, 98, 72, 0.15);
  }

  .b2h-insight__icon {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 2px;
  }

  .b2h-insight__text {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .b2h-insight__text strong {
    color: var(--accent-brown-light);
  }
</style>
